  15 Nov 2005; Henrik Brix Andersen <brix@gentoo.org>
  orinoco-0.15_rc2-r2.ebuild:
  Instruct user to use the in-kernel module for linux-2.6.15+.

  28 May 2005; <brix@gentoo.org> -orinoco-0.15_rc2.ebuild,
  -orinoco-0.15_rc2-r1.ebuild:
  Pruned old ebuilds.

  23 May 2005; <brix@gentoo.org> orinoco-0.15_rc2-r2.ebuild:
  Stable on x86.

*orinoco-0.15_rc2-r2 (28 Apr 2005)

  28 Apr 2005; <brix@gentoo.org> +files/orinoco-0.15rc2-firmware.patch,
  +orinoco-0.15_rc2-r2.ebuild:
  Fixed bug #69929 and bug #78366.

  07 Jan 2005; Henrik Brix Andersen <brix@gentoo.org>
  +files/orinoco-0.15rc2-2.6.10.patch, orinoco-0.15_rc2-r1.ebuild:
  Allow compiling against kernel 2.6.10, fixes bug #76979.

  04 Jan 2005; Henrik Brix Andersen <brix@gentoo.org>
  orinoco-0.15_rc2-r1.ebuild:
  Use MODULESD_ORINOCO_DOCS for installing README.orinoco.

*orinoco-0.15_rc2-r1 (04 Jan 2005)

  04 Jan 2005; Henrik Brix Andersen <brix@gentoo.org>
  +orinoco-0.15_rc2-r1.ebuild:
  Ported to use linux-mod.eclass, bumping because of modules.d file additions.

  01 Nov 2004; Henrik Brix Andersen <brix@gentoo.org> +metadata.xml:
  Initial check-in, ebuild by me. Thanks to all who commented on bug #57031.

